For {= source_family =}+ distinct official issuing-source families, name {= opportunity =}+ specific public climate-hardtech opportunities per family that were active as of {= snapshot_date =}, with at least {= url =} public URL from an official issuer-controlled or primary issuing surface for each opportunity.

Each opportunity should be a responder-actionable public call: grant, NOFO/FOA, procurement/tender, RFP/RFQ/RFO/offtake call, demo or pilot call, prize, innovation competition, or comparable public opportunity. Use the issuer plus native identifier when public: solicitation number, FOA/NOFO ID, SAM notice ID, TED notice ID, UNGM reference, MDB notice ID, call identifier, RFP/RFO number, or equivalent; if no public identifier exists, the issuer and opportunity title must still isolate one concrete opportunity.

The source family named for an opportunity must match the cited surface. Official central portals count as primary issuing surfaces when they are the system of record, including SAM.gov, Grants.gov/Simpler, EU Funding and Tenders, TED, UNGM, multilateral development bank procurement portals, official state or national energy-office pages, official funder procurement pages, issuer-owned RFP/RFO pages, and public innovation-competition portals. Commercial aggregators and advisory products are discovery-only and should not be used as final evidence: DevelopmentAid, GlobalTenders, fundsforngos, Starbase, OpenGrants, grant-writing pages, lead-generation pages, procurement-intelligence pages, scraper products, and bid-advice pages are not primary evidence.

Suitable hardtech domains include clean power, storage, hydrogen, carbon removal, industrial decarbonization, grid hardware/software tied to physical deployment, building or transport electrification, charging infrastructure, clean fuels, water/energy adaptation infrastructure, and similar climate-relevant hardware or infrastructure work. Do not include policy pledges, award notices, press releases about past awards, evergreen funder relationship pages, generic funding-program pages without a current call, closed famous programs, recommendation/advice content, lead scoring, vendor matching, ranking, applicant strategy, contact enrichment, or bid desirability judgments.

Requirements:
- The page must identify the specific claimed opportunity through issuer plus native identifier, title, solicitation number, notice ID, call ID, or another opportunity-specific anchor.
- The page must be on an official issuer-controlled surface or primary issuing surface for that opportunity, not a commercial aggregator, advisory product, lead-generation page, scraper, press-wire copy, bid-advice page, grant-writing page, or procurement-intelligence summary.
- The page must show that the cited surface belongs to the claimed source family; a valid family label is not enough when the URL and page are from a different source family.
- The page must carry dated status, deadline, opening, posting, amendment, closing, inactive-date, or preserved-snapshot evidence that can be compared to {= snapshot_date =}; a bare "Open" or "Active" label is not enough without date-bearing official support.
- The page must tie the opportunity to climate-relevant hardtech, infrastructure, equipment, deployment, demonstration, applied R&D, offtake, or physical-system operations.
- The page must communicate a public response mechanism: bid, proposal, application, quotation, offer, competition entry, expression of interest, RFO/offtake response, or comparable responder action.
